    TH_ISO14443_4_Maxim_MAX66000, TH_ISO14443_4_Maxim_MAX66020, TH_ISO14443_4_Maxim_MAX66040

    public class TH_ISO14443_4_Maxim
extends TH_ISO14443_4
    Base class for ISO14443-4 transponder of manufacturer MAXIM.
    This class supports only addressed and selected mode in Host-Mode
    .
    Description:
    High-level class for easy-to-use Transponder specific communication. See ITagGroup for additional information.

    Note: Programmers should be familiar with the ISO 14443 standards.

    • Method Detail

      • getSystemInformation

        public int getSystemInformation(TH_Maxim_Result result)
                         throws java.lang.Exception,
                                FeException
        Get System Information command
        Parameters:
        result - TH_Maxim_Result object containing return values
        Returns:
        operation status
        • 0 if OK
        • > 0 status byte of the responded protocol, if the Reader signals a problem. See Reader's System Manual for the full list with all status bytes
        Throws:
        FeException - exception with error code (<0)
        java.lang.Exception -
        Description:
        Command execution realized with [0xB2][0xBE] T=CL - APDU command
        The result object of type TH_Maxim_Result contains only valid data, if the operation status is 0.

        Detailed description about the command and the parameters can be found in:
        - Product Datasheet for MAX66000, MAX66020 or MAX66040 from MAXIM
